# FASTQ Quality Parser

A lightweight, dependency-minimal Python tool for FASTQ quality control analysis.
Parses raw sequencing reads and generates a per-base quality report + multi-panel QC plot —
without needing FastQC installed.

---   

## Features

- Per-base Phred quality score statistics (mean, median, IQR)
- Read length distribution
- GC content per read
- N-base frequency
- Pass / Warn / Fail quality flags
- Plain-text summary report
- 4-panel QC plot (PNG)
- Supports plain `.fastq` and compressed `.fastq.gz`
- Optional read limit for quick previews of large files

---

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/fastq-quality-parser.git
cd fastq-quality-parser
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**Requirements:**
```
numpy
matplotlib
```

---

## Usage

```bash
# Basic usage
python fastq_quality_parser.py -i sample.fastq -o qc_output/

# Gzip input
python fastq_quality_parser.py -i sample.fastq.gz -o qc_output/

# Limit to first 50,000 reads (fast preview)
python fastq_quality_parser.py -i large_sample.fastq.gz -o qc_output/ --max-reads 50000
```

